      "date": "2015-10-05 17:24:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nThe code that places the peer datastructures on a specific CPT has\nthe issue that you ought to pick the CPT (and preferably the node,\nwhen CPT != node) after you've picked the preferred interface to use\nto talk to that peer, and know which node that interface lives in.\nBut that's another discussion.\n\nWhat I do see this code doing is follow the same placement rules\nthat LNet uses for the socklnd-specific datastructures, which is\nat least an improvement over the status quo.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
